@johnthackara:

So I read "Huawei delivers advanced AI chip 'cluster' to Chinese clients cut off from Nvidia" - and this is what one looks like https://www.ft.com/... [image]

I’m listening to this Intel talk about uOps, and they are going through an example where they optimize this code:

for (int i = 0; i < 4096; i++)
    m = max(m, x[i]);

They’re talking about how using SIMD can make this faster, but this loop seems obviously memory bandwidth limited, so I’m confused

